              <p>Insomnia is a sleeping disorder with difficulty falling asleep. People with this wake up often during the night and have trouble going back to sleep. Most of this is related to poor sleeping habits, depression, anxiety, or certain medications.</p>
              <p>Acute insomnia may not need treatment, but mild insomnia can be prevented with good sleep habits. Short acting drugs can help avoid effects such as drowsiness. Chronic insomnia includes first treating underlying conditions or health problems. Relaxation exercises, sleep restriction therapy, and reconditioning can also help.</p>

